{
  "texts": [
    "Moreover, an ancestor search algorithm is outlined to find the most similar ancestor in the taxonomy of the known classes.",
    "For standard classification, Ghadimi Atigh et al. (2021) show how to integrate uniformity amongst prototypes in hyperbolic space by embedding classes with maximum separation on the boundary of the Poincaré ball given by Mettes et al. (2019); Kasarla et al. (2022).",
    "With prototypes now at the boundary of the ball, standard distance functions no longer apply since they are at the infinite distance to any point within the ball.",
    "To that end, they propose to use the Busemann distance, which is given for hyperbolic image embedding g(x) and prototype p as:",
    "By fixing prototypes with maximum separation a priori and minimizing this distance function with an extra regularization towards the origin, it becomes possible to perform hyperbolic prototypical learning with prototypes at the ideal boundary."
  ]
}